                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d687">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890D.927/141: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Beirut</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-11T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 11, 1941—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>32. Your No. 52, February 27, 9 a.m. The Embassy at Vichy is being instructed by
                    mail to make a formal reservation of the rights of the Oriental Institute and to
                    express the confidence of the American Government that the Government of France
                    will not accede to the German Government’s request that the contract be
                    cancelled.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
